You: "No, we don't." [Leave.]
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, no. We are talking about it. I was able to re-contextualize it as a dark joke." He pauses thoughtfully. "I will not be able to re-contextualize it the next time."
You: "It's going to happen again. I'm going to do it again. I'm going try it again *soon*."
"It will happen again. Until I succeed. Suicide is painless."

Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes. Well. I was able to re-contextualize it as a *dark joke*." He pauses thoughtfully. "I will not be able to re-contextualize it the next time."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I understand you sometimes employ *extreme* interrogation tactics, but I want you to understand: that was *too* extreme."
You: "Do we have to?"

Kim Kitsuragi: "The Gloaming?" He takes off his glasses and cleans them. "Now, that's exactly what we *can't* have. Couldn't have put it better myself. I would need to *re-contextualize* the hell out of that."
Kim Kitsuragi: He puts his glasses back on. "Now, let's go. And let's keep guns out of our mouths. And not say anything about any gloaming, or anything like that."
You: "I wished to embrace The Gloaming ahead of time. The undoing of the atoms called to me."
You: "It was a cry for help."
Kim Kitsuragi: He puts his glasses back on and repeats: "Never. Now, let's go."
Suggestion: This was your chance to make amends, but you chose not to. Instead you chose to be the bad-ass suicide boiadeiro and now he doesn't like you.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good. I'm glad we had this talk." He nods. "After you."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Whooh..." He takes off his glasses, reaches for a cloth -- pauses -- and puts his glasses back on.
Suggestion: He has an idea who *she* is. Many cops have a *she* or *he* who left. But he just doesn't know what to say.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know why she left you. Let's go."
